Exercise can be done sitting or standing. With a lightweight dumbbell or water bottle in each hand, move your arms to the side until they are horizontal. The hand rest should point upwards and the elbows must be slightly bent.

Standing with your face against a wall, and just as an arm\'s distance from the wall, put your palms against the wall at shoulder height. The elbows bend so the nose almost touches the wall - elbows stretch again.

It is pulled up with a leg on a staircase or a low stool. There is pulled up so that the other foot is just put on the step and immediately after putting down again. The front foot is held on the step until the set number of repetitions is completed. Then put the other foot on the step.

Standing with the back against a chair, you sit down on the chair, but without sitting down on the seat. Once you have moved as far down as the balance allows you, get up again. The hands are held at your side.
Lie on the back of the floor with a bend in the hip and knee joint and the soles of the feet flat in the floor. The arms are placed across the chest. Head and shoulders lifted from the floor.
If you are sitting, stand up and start walking while standing in the same place for 60 seconds.
If you are sitting, stand up and go for a walk for about 5-10 minuttes. This can be done outside for extra relaxation.

Sitting or standing, hold both arms over the head and move the upper body over to one side until a stretch is felt down the opposite side. This position is kept as long as possible. Then do the same with the opposite page.
If you are seated, get up. Now bend your upper body forward and stretch out your toes with as stretched legs as possible. Hold this position for 30-60 seconds.
Now it\'s on with the tracksuit and running shoes. It is now time to run 5 km. This can be done either outside or on a treadmill. It\'s all up to you.
Now it\'s on with the tracksuit and running shoes. It is now time to run 10 km. This can be done either outside or on a treadmill. It\'s all up to you.

Place yourself on the floor with stretched arms and stretched legs. Now bend the elbows so the body moves up and down the floor. Perform this exercise until you have reached 50 pieces. There must be short breaks between.

It\'s a bit like running on the spot, instead you raise your knees high up so they are completely horizontal. Spread well into your core while you are spurring with the high knees, so give it a little extra to the stomach too. Make as many as possible in 45 seconds
